=================================================
 
A heart-warming comedy following two unlikely young parents-to-be.


Pramface is a BBC Three television comedy series starring Scarlett Alice Johnson, Sean Michael Verey, Ben Crompton, Bronagh Gallagher, Anna Chancellor and Angus Deayton. 

Written by Chris Reddy and produced by BBC/Little Comet,the six-part first series commenced transmission on 23 February 2012. 
The second series began on 8 January 2013, with the first episode 60 minutes long, as a special, and the remainder of the series consisted of the usual 30 minute episodes. The second series concluded on 19 February 2013. A third series was confirmed on 29 April 2013.




1/7 Laura and Jamie welcome their new addition to the family.

2/7 Laura and Jamie welcome their new addition to the family.

3/7 Jamie is forced to leave Emily with his last resort babysitters, Mike and Beth.

4/7 Mike organises Jamie's 18th. Keith goes on a New Age-influenced 'back to work' course.

5/7 When Laura learns that Jamie has a date, she goes out of her way to get one herself.

6/7 Danielle invites Laura to a university ball, while both Jamie and Keith are at a low ebb.

7/7 Jamie and Laura are now officially a couple, but Laura won't go public with the news.
